Suebis. In G. 38, 1 (where see note) this is a generic name for a very large number of German tribes, living mostly east of the Elbe; but the name (taken to mean ‘wanderers') is one that may be vaguely used. Gantrelle has pointed out that those here meant must be on the coast of Holland aud would answer to those spoken of in Suet. Aug. 21, ‘ Suebos et Sigambros dedentes se traduxit in Galliam, atque in proximis Rheno agris collocavit.'
